Let $p(x)=x^2+qx+r$ and $q(x)=x^2+sx+t$. Thus, we have
\begin{align*} p^2 &=x^4+2qx^3+(2r+q^2)x^2+(2rq)x+r^2=x^4+ax^3+bx^2+cx+1, \\ q^2 &=x^4+2sx^3+(2t+s^2)x^2+(2st)x+t^2=x^4+2ax^3+2bx^2+2cx+1. \end{align*}
Comparing coefficients, we get
\begin{align*} 2q&=a, \\ 2r+q^2&=b, \\ 2rq&=c, \\ r^2&=1, \\ 2s&=2a, \\ 2t+s^2&=2b, \\ 2st&=2c, \\ t^2&=1. \end{align*}
Thus, $r=t=1$, $c=2q$, $b=2q+1$, and $a=2q$, so $2q+2q+2q+1=\boxed{6q+1}$ is our desired answer.
